    <h1>The Nomo FOMO Story</h1>
    <p>While in Bogota, two travel enthusiasts who just finished Remote Year were talking about how hard it was to keep track of their friend's and family's travels.  Between the number of people who were traveling as digital nomads and others who lived abroad, there was no tool that allowed them to coordinate this information.  From this, the idea of Nomo FOMO came about as the tool that allows you to keep track of your personal travel as well as your friends' travel plans so you can meet up with each other and continue to travel together as much as possible.  Of course, they didn't stop there, but continued to focus on other pain points in fellow travelers experiences to build out your ultimate travel network.</p>
